item.title: [RAT-354] Integration tests fail with new Maven 4.0.0-alpha-12
item.description:
Running the newly published

Unable to find source-code formatter for language: shell. item.summary: Integration tests fail with new Maven 4.0.0-alpha-12

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
pottlinger do you know if 4.0.0 allows element properties? For example would we be able to do:

<configuration>
<license>
<license id='foo'>
<text>find me</text>
</license>
</license>
</configuration>

I've got no idea, sorry.

cstamas can you help out from the Maven-point of view? Thanks.

The IT fails because the output contains the following warning:

[WARNING] Version not locked for default bindings plugins [maven-clean-plugin], you should define versions in pluginManagement section of your pom.xml or parent

The version must be defined for that plugin in order to get rid of the warning.
